article.description: — D’Maurian Williams had a career-best 21 points as Gardner-Webb beat Charleston Southern 74-62 on Sunday.
article.headline: Williams carries Gardner-Webb over Charleston Southern 74-62
article.linkText: Williams carries Gardner-Webb over Charleston Southern 74-62
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. -- — D’Maurian Williams had a career-best 21 points as Gardner-Webb beat Charleston Southern 74-62 on Sunday. This series was originally set for Jan 4-5 and was moved up when South Carolina Upstate couldn't play at Gardner-Webb. Jordan Sears had 16 points for Gardner-Webb (5-9, 4-5 Big South Conference). Kareem Reid added 13 points and 11 rebounds. Jaheam Cornwall had seven assists. Gardner-Webb posted a season-high 22 assists. Phlandrous Fleming Jr. had 32 points and seven rebounds for the Buccaneers (1-12, 0-9), who have now lost nine games in a row. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
